ngram\": \"only 35%\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2236}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic overseers\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2285}, {\"ngram\": \"the likelihood\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2316}, {\"ngram\": \"the largest religious population\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2377}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2391}, {\"ngram\": \"its viewing audience\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amassive global boycottis exactly what resulted.\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2484, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Amassive global boycottis\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2461}, {\"ngram\": \"exactly what\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2474}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And those who paid and pay the price are all the amazing Olympic athletes from every country in every sport who have worked for years with heart and perseverance to get to that stage of competition.\", \"from\": 2485, \"to\": 2683, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the price\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2521}, {\"ngram\": \"all the amazing Olympic athletes\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2558}, {\"ngram\": \"every country\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2577}, {\"ngram\": \"every sport\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2592}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2618}, {\"ngram\": \"heart\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2629}, {\"ngram\": \"perseverance\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2646}, {\"ngram\": \"that stage\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2667}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2682}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not misunderstand me.\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2709, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not homophobic.\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2730, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I believe in America we must embrace diversity.\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 2778, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 2744, \"to\": 2751}, {\"ngram\": \"diversity\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2777}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, America was founded upon it.\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2815, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2794}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, what happens when promoting diversity and inclusion denigrates and even desecrates others' core convictions or religious practices?\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2957, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"diversity\", \"from\": 2854, \"to\": 2863}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2877}, {\"ngram\": \"others' core convictions\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"religious practices\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 2956}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do DEI advocates, including those overseeing the Olympics, expect others to tolerate (and even embrace)theirviews while they denigrate others before a global audience?\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 3126, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"DEI advocates\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 2975}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3016}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3031}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3100}, {\"ngram\": \"a global audience\", \"from\": 3108, \"to\": 3125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Justifying one's freedom to act should not warrant stepping all over others who differ from you.\", \"from\": 3127, \"to\": 3223, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one's freedom\", \"from\": 3138, \"to\": 3151}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3202}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Does not diversity go both ways?\", \"from\": 3224, \"to\": 3256, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"diversity\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3242}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Democracy is not mob rule, and yet so often modern Americans (and those in other western countries) interpret it that way: \\\"If you do not believe as we do, we will force our convictions upon you, using social, economic, legal, emotional and any other type of pressure until you consent in agreement and conformity.\\\"\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3573, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Democracy\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3267}, {\"ngram\": \"mob rule\", \"from\": 3275, \"to\": 3283}, {\"ngram\": \"yet so often modern Americans\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3318}, {\"ngram\": \"other western countries\", \"from\": 3333, \"to\": 3356}, {\"ngram\": \"our convictions\", \"from\": 3428, \"to\": 3443}, {\"ngram\": \"any other type\", \"from\": 3499, \"to\": 3513}, {\"ngram\": \"pressure\", \"from\": 3517, \"to\": 3525}, {\"ngram\": \"agreement\", \"from\": 3547, \"to\": 3556}, {\"ngram\": \"conformity\", \"from\": 3561, \"to\": 3571}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(I encourage you subscribe and read the latest edition of theWhistleblower, \\\"America's All-Out Religious War,\\\" which details many other anti-religious incidents in society like the above.)\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3763, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the latest edition\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3629}, {\"ngram\": \"theWhistleblower\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3649}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"America's All-Out Religious War\", \"from\": 3651, \"to\": 3683}, {\"ngram\": \"many other anti-religious incidents\", \"from\": 3700, \"to\": 3735}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 3739, \"to\": 3746}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The second Olympic fracture last week erupted when the Algerian boxer Imane Khelif, who was deemed to have male XY chromosomes (be biologically male) thoughregistered as a woman,won a fight in just 46 secondsin the 66-kilogram women's division againstItaly's Angela Carini.\", \"from\": 3765, \"to\": 4038, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3820, \"end\": 3828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999010488003, \"rank\": 9.891801626384905e-08, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 3835, \"end\": 3847, \"title\": \